eplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=191.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: emergence of the seeker</span><hr size=1> Bare feet left a red trail through the streets of Neriak.  Audible gasps were followed by silent parading behind the Reaper of the Violent Harvest.  Creapiing walked steadily, shoulders and head held firmly upright, eyes fixed on the future.  The eerie procession trailed silently behind her and carefully avoided her mark on the streets.  The path she chose this morning was one that she had intended to follow earlier.  This was the way to her favorite fishing spot.<br>
<br>
<br>
Creapiing stood on a boulder, next to the shore of the lake, and spread her arms wide.  She forced her body to become as rigid as death.  Then slowly, to the outcry of the crowd, she allowed herself to fall.<br>
<br>
Red gore, blood, ink, boiled up behind her and clouded the water.  <br>
<br>
The procession stood uncertain for a moment, then one brave Teir'dal jumped into the water.  The splash awoke the charmed onlookers.  Many jumped .  With each addition the water stirred the redness more until the children of Innoruuk floated in a sea of blood.<br>
<br>
